messages.message: Has anyone run into a `[Errno 2] No such file or directory` error when trying to run a goldens test locally? The command I'm using is `make run-golden-test-runner TOKEN=iXIfWDGptpPrbl30KZ02W6nmWlTe6i USERNAME=goldens-tester TEST_ENV=localhost IB_TEST_ENV=local INPUT_PATH='ib_eng/tests/fs/Test Drive' TEST_NAMES='bank-statements-test'`, which works when the test_env is `dogfood.instabase.com (http://dogfood.instabase.com)`. All services in `ppy status lite` are up, and I've tried recompiling and restarting core-platform-service and grpc-file-service. Does anyone have tips for how to fix?
